    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-23T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-23T05:00:00-05:00" n="162"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/9888</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-23T12:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1918, 12 noon.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 24, 2.11 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1948. War Trade Board, Bureau Enemy Trade [from <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_JS1">Stewart</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 2. Referring your No. 163, July 2, to <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName>.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d162fn1">See footnote 3, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_1030">p. 1030</ref>.</note> At his request have conferred
                    with Italian Foreign Office in regard to acceptance by Italy of War Trade Board
                    resolution of April 29, concerning enemy trading license committees. Am now
                    advised that Italy will accept principle of this resolution but acceptance is
                    limited to licenses for trading with listed persons. Italy will submit such
                    applications to proposed committees but will not agree to submit applications
                    for licenses to trade with enemy persons not listed. <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_JS1">Stewart</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jay</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
